      <h2>Best RuPay Credit Cards in India</h2>
      <p>RuPay credit cards have emerged as a powerful alternative to Visa and Mastercard in the Indian market. Operated by NPCI (National Payments Corporation of India), the same organisation behind UPI, RuPay cards offer unique advantages that international networks cannot match — most notably, seamless UPI integration that lets you use your credit card for scan-and-pay QR code transactions at 300+ million UPI merchant locations across India.</p>
      <p>RuPay cards also benefit from lower processing costs for banks (resulting in more competitive fees and rewards), government-backed personal accident insurance, and eligibility for exclusive government scheme benefits. With major banks like HDFC, SBI, ICICI, and Axis now issuing RuPay credit cards, the network offers a full range from entry-level to premium variants.</p>

      <h2>Key Features of RuPay Credit Cards</h2>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>UPI Integration:</strong> Link your RuPay credit card to Google Pay, PhonePe, Paytm, and BHIM for QR-code payments</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Government Benefits:</strong> Complimentary personal accident insurance of ₹1-10 lakh under PMJDY and related schemes</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Lower Transaction Costs:</strong> RuPay's lower MDR means banks pass on savings through better rewards and lower fees</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Domestic Acceptance:</strong> Accepted at 100% of POS terminals in India including small shops and rural merchants</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit on UPI:</strong> Earn credit card rewards on UPI QR payments — a feature unique to RuPay credit cards</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Data Sovereignty:</strong> All transaction data processed within India — enhanced privacy and security compliance</li>
      </ul>

