      <h2>Eligibility for RuPay Credit Cards</h2>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Age:</strong> 21-60 years (salaried) or 21-65 years (self-employed); student cards available from 18 years</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Income:</strong> ₹15,000/month for basic RuPay cards; ₹25,000+ for premium RuPay variants</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit Score:</strong> 680+ CIBIL for most RuPay credit cards; secured options available for lower scores</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>UPI App:</strong> Must have a UPI-enabled app (Google Pay, PhonePe, etc.) to leverage UPI credit card benefits</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Employment:</strong> Salaried, self-employed, business owners, and students with documented income or guarantor</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Documents:</strong> PAN Card, Aadhaar Card, income proof, bank statement, and passport-size photograph</li>
      </ul>

