  <section class="faq-section"><div class="container">
    <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">FAQs</span><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><p>Common questions about RuPay credit cards and UPI integration</p></div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">How do I link my RuPay credit card to UPI?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">To link your RuPay credit card to UPI: (1) Open your UPI app (Google Pay, PhonePe, or Paytm), (2) Go to "Payment Methods" or "Add Payment Method", (3) Select "Credit Card on UPI" or "RuPay Credit Card", (4) Choose your bank and enter the card details, (5) Verify with OTP sent to your registered mobile number. Once linked, a new UPI ID is created for your credit card. When paying via UPI, simply select the credit card account instead of your bank account. All transactions are charged to your credit card limit and earn card rewards.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Can I earn rewards on UPI payments with a RuPay credit card?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes! This is one of the biggest advantages of RuPay credit cards. When you pay via UPI using your linked RuPay credit card, you earn the same reward points or cashback as you would on a regular card swipe. For example, if your HDFC UPI RuPay card offers 5% on UPI spends, you earn that on every QR scan-and-pay transaction at tea stalls, grocery shops, restaurants, and any other UPI merchant. This was impossible before RuPay credit on UPI, as Visa/Mastercard UPI integration is still limited. It effectively turns every small payment into a reward-earning opportunity.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Can RuPay credit cards be used internationally?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Standard RuPay credit cards are primarily designed for domestic use and may not work at international merchant terminals or foreign websites. However, RuPay has partnered with Discover and JCB networks, enabling select RuPay cards to work internationally in countries where Discover/JCB are accepted (USA, Japan, South Korea, and 190+ countries). RuPay Select and RuPay Premium cards offer better international coverage. For frequent international travellers, pairing a RuPay card (for UPI domestic benefits) with a Visa/Mastercard (for international acceptance) is the optimal strategy.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">What is the free accident insurance on RuPay cards?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">All RuPay cardholders receive complimentary personal accident insurance under the NPCI scheme: RuPay Classic cards provide ₹1 lakh coverage, RuPay Platinum cards provide ₹2 lakh, and RuPay Select/Premium cards provide up to ₹10 lakh in personal accident cover. This insurance is completely free and activates automatically with any successful transaction (minimum ₹1) within 90 days before the accident. No separate enrollment or premium payment is needed. This is a unique benefit not offered by Visa or Mastercard networks on their standard cards.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Why should I choose RuPay over Visa or Mastercard?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Choose RuPay if: (1) You primarily spend domestically and want UPI credit card integration, (2) You make frequent small payments at local merchants via QR codes and want to earn rewards on those, (3) You value lower processing fees (which translate to better rewards), (4) You want free government-backed accident insurance, (5) You prefer data sovereignty with all transactions processed within India. Choose Visa/Mastercard if: international acceptance is critical, you travel abroad frequently, or you need specific international network benefits. Many savvy consumers hold both — RuPay for UPI-heavy domestic spending and Visa/Mastercard for international use.</div></div></div>
    </div>
